-- ConocoPhillips Flares Sulfur Dioxide From Belle Chasse Refinery
-- Clyde Russell
-- 2010-09-07T05:49:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-07/conocophillips-flares-sulfur-dioxide-from-belle-chasse-refinery.html

          
          
             ConocoPhillips flared sulfur dioxide
from its refinery at Belle Chasse, Louisiana, after shutting
part of a sulfur unit for repairs, according to a filing to the
National Response Center. The incident started at 4:04 p.m.
local time yeesterday, the report said.  
 U.S. refineries must notify the National Response Center if
they release hazardous substance in excess of reportable
quantities, according to the Comprehensive Environmental
Response, Compensation and Liability Act, commonly known as
Superfund.  
          
          


  


        